  "name": "state_machine_3",
  "description": "3-state mutual exclusion machine. Each state is a bistable ring (3 CH neurons, a=0/c=-65/d=0). States: A, B, C. Only one active at a time. Each trigger RS both activates its state AND kills the other two via shared FS kill neurons. Cross-inhibition from active state's CH output continuously drives the other states' FS kills, maintaining exclusion after trigger ends. State transitions are clean: trigger new state -> old state dies within 2-3 ticks -> new state sustains indefinitely. Use case: behavioral repertoire (Forward/Backward/Pause), mode selection, finite automata.",
